# UI Components Rules (shadcn/ui)

## CRITICAL - Common Runtime Errors

### Select: Empty String Values

Select components cannot use `value=""`. Radix UI reserves empty string for "no selection".

❌ **Causes runtime error:**
```typescript
<SelectItem value="">None</SelectItem>
<SelectItem value={item.id}> // where item.id might be ""
```

✅ **Use placeholder value:**
```typescript
<SelectItem value="none">None</SelectItem>
<SelectItem value={item.id || "none"}>

// Convert in handlers:
value={category || "none"}
onValueChange={(v) => setCategory(v === "none" ? "" : v)}
```

## Selection Hierarchy

1. **Check existing** `components/ui/` first
2. **Install from registry** if not present: `npx shadcn@latest add [component]`
3. **Combine existing** components before creating custom
4. **Create custom** only as last resort (follow shadcn patterns)

## Installed Components

Available in `components/ui/`:
- Alert, Avatar, Badge, Button, Card
- Dialog, DropdownMenu, Form, Input, Label
- PasswordInput, Select, Separator, Table
- Tabs, Toast, Toaster, Checkbox

## Common Request Mappings

| User Request | Use Component |
|-------------|---------------|
| "modal", "popup" | Dialog |
| "dropdown", "menu" | DropdownMenu or Select |
| "notification" | Toast |
| "loading" | Skeleton or Loader2 (lucide) |
| "sidebar", "drawer" | Sheet (install if needed) |
| "tooltip" | Tooltip (install if needed) |
| "toggle", "switch" | Switch (install if needed) |
| "data table" | Table with pagination |
| "date picker" | Calendar (install if needed) |
| "autocomplete" | Command (install if needed) |

## Installation

```bash
# Single component
npx shadcn@latest add dialog

# Multiple components
npx shadcn@latest add dialog sheet tooltip

# Update all
npx shadcn@latest update
```

## Usage Pattern

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogTrigger } from "@/components/ui/dialog"
```

## Styling Rules

1. Use component's built-in variants (`variant="destructive"`, `size="sm"`)
2. Extend with `className` using Tailwind utilities
3. Never use inline styles or separate CSS files

## Component Gotchas

### Dialog: Controlled vs Uncontrolled

**Uncontrolled** (simple, self-contained):
```typescript
<Dialog>
  <DialogTrigger asChild><Button>Open</Button></DialogTrigger>
  <DialogContent>...</DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```

**Controlled** (when you need to close programmatically):
```typescript
const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);

<Button onClick={() => setOpen(true)}>Open</Button>
<Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen}>
  <DialogContent>
    <YourForm onSuccess={() => setOpen(false)} />
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```

⚠️ Never mix: Don't use `DialogTrigger` inside a controlled Dialog

### Select: No Empty Strings

Radix Select doesn't allow `value=""`:
```typescript
// ❌ <SelectItem value="">None</SelectItem>
// ✅ <SelectItem value="none">None</SelectItem>

// Convert in handlers:
value={category || "none"}
onValueChange={(v) => setCategory(v === "none" ? "" : v)}
```

### Client Components: Hydration Mismatch

Components using browser APIs (`window`, `localStorage`, `document`) must wait for mount:

```typescript
"use client"
const [mounted, setMounted] = useState(false)
useEffect(() => setMounted(true), [])

if (!mounted) return null  // or <Skeleton />

// Now safe to use browser APIs
const width = window.innerWidth
```

**When to use this pattern:**
- Accessing `window.*` or `document.*`
- Reading `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`
- Viewport/position calculations
- Theme-dependent rendering with `useTheme()`
- Any value that differs between server and client

> ⚠️ Without this pattern, React hydration will fail because server-rendered HTML
> won't match client-rendered output (server has no `window` object).

## Anti-Patterns

❌ Installing Material-UI, Ant Design, or other UI libraries
❌ Writing custom modals without checking Dialog
❌ Creating custom form inputs without Form primitives
❌ Using vanilla HTML inputs without Input styling
❌ Implementing custom toast systems
❌ Writing CSS modules or styled-components
❌ Using `DialogTrigger` inside a controlled Dialog (with `open={}` prop)
❌ Using empty string values in Select components (`value=""`)
❌ Using `window`/`localStorage`/`document` without the mounted state pattern

## Response Template

When implementing UI:
1. "I'll use the existing [component] from shadcn/ui"
2. "Let me install [component] from shadcn/ui"
3. "I'll combine [component1] and [component2]"
4. Only if none exist: "I'll create a custom component following shadcn patterns"
